The one exception: if you're running a single location with a dedicated sales team and need enterprise reporting, HubSpot Professional is the better CRM. You're paying more for a better product in that specific scenario. But the moment you add locations, the math flips decisively in GHL's favor.

<h2 id="verdict">Final Recommendation</h2>

<div class="verdict-box">
  <h3>Agency Unlimited at $297/mo -- the operator tier</h3>
  <p>Stop evaluating the other plans. If you're a multi-location operator, Agency Unlimited is the only tier that makes sense. Unlimited sub-accounts and Snapshots are the features that make GHL a category of one for operators -- and they're only available on Agency Unlimited and above. Budget $330-390/mo total when you factor in SMS and phone usage. At even 5 locations, you're paying less per location than any comparable CRM setup.</p>
